Make user-facing messages read like tool output

First pass: rewrite CLI errors, warnings, and prompts that read like
generated prose: dash- and semicolon-joined clauses, "successfully" and
"Please" filler, redundant hand-holding sentences, and a "Configuration
error:" preamble that anyhow already frames. Replace forbidden unicode
ellipses in the kubernetes exec errors and an adjacent comment.

Second pass: normalize casing. The codebase mixed capitalized and
lowercase messages; lowercase already dominated, so lowercase the
leading word of the remaining capitalized errors and progress lines.
Proper nouns and acronyms (Docker, Kubernetes, Claude, SSH, URL, HTTP
methods, DNS-1123, ...), table headers, and git's difftool-mimic prompts
keep their case.

Behaviour is unchanged. Tests that matched the reworded or recased
strings are updated.
